The former Finance Minister was axed by President Jacob Zuma four days after being ordered to return from an investor roadshow in London. PRETORIA - President Jacob Zuma has wielded the axe, firing Pravin Gordhan as Finance Minister, his deputy Mcebisi Jonas, Tourism Minister Derek Hanekom, Transport Minister Dipuo Peters and Public Service and Administration Minister Ngoako Ramatlhodi in one of his most dramatic moves during his time in the Union Buildings.The President announced 20 changes to his cabinet, with former ANC Youth League president Malusi Gigaba replacing Gordhan, while Sifiso Buthelezi will fill Jonas's position.WATCH: Pravin Gordhan comment on his axing